div.p:
How could one prove more clearly than I have proved that we are the object of a
                    malicious charge; that the evidence brought forward against my opponent is true;
                    and that his condemnation was just? I have shown that he refused to examine by
                    torture the slave who wrote the testimony regarding the very things to which he
                    had testified; that his brother, Aesius, has attested the facts which he on his
                    part declares to be false;
